verses.text: The \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*reigneth, he is clothed with majesty; the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*is clothed with strength, wherewithhe hath girded himself: the world also is stablished, that it cannot be moved.
Thy throne isestablished of old: thou artfrom everlasting.
The floods have lifted up, O \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*, the floods have lifted up their voice; the floods lift up their waves.
The \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*on high ismightier than the noise of many waters, yea, thanthe mighty waves of the sea.
Thy testimonies are very sure: holiness becometh thine house, O \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*, for ever.
